<subSubSection pageId="110" pageNumber="111" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="110.[151,1436,639,1026]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,416,855,881]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Biology and notes.</emphasis>
Probably an introduced species. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[902,997,856,881]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[902,997,856,881]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Paragus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs throughout all continents. In the New World, seven species have been recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[741,814,891,917]" country="Canada" name="Yukon" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Yukon</collectingRegion>
to Central America. This is the first record of this tribe and genus in southern South America. We do not know the flowers that this species visits, the prey they consume in their larval stages, or the basic aspects of its biology and ecology.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="110.[151,1436,639,1026]" box="[199,1075,999,1026]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,443,999,1025]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Conservation status.</emphasis>
Not evaluated because this species is considered exotic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
